    "lastUpdated": "May 2026",
    "methodology": "Each role reports two fully-loaded employer cost scenarios. The local_scenario uses the local employer base salary from salaries-philippines.json (Glassdoor/Payscale/Indeed sources). The us_remote_scenario uses the US employer remote base salary from salaries-philippines.json (Arc.dev or BLS OES May 2024 offshore-discount estimate). Both scenarios apply identical statutory rates and operational costs. SSS employer contribution is 10% of monthly salary credit (MSC), capped at $57/month (MSC ceiling of ₱35,000). PhilHealth employer contribution is 2.5% of monthly salary, uncapped below the ₱100,000/month ($1,623) salary base ceiling (capped at $41/month above that base). Pag-IBIG employer contribution is $3/month (cap reached at ₱10,000/month base). 13th month pay modeled as 8.33% of monthly base salary (1/12 of annual basic). Equipment amortized over 36 months. Management overhead is an industry-typical estimate (7.5% of base salary) for organizations using managed remote workforce providers."
  },
